  "_comment": "Approved aliases: what labs print -> the canonical analyte in the master sheet. Hand-curated and merged into the codebook at load time, so re-importing the sheet never clobbers it. An LLM may PROPOSE an entry here; only a human may add one. Get this wrong silently and a 15-year trend becomes three different tests.",
  "_matching_note": "Matching is token-containment, so an alias only needs the distinguishing words; 'HbA1c' already catches 'HbA1c (Glycosylated Hemoglobin)'. Aliases exist for names that share NO tokens with the canonical (SGOT/AST), or where the canonical has a typo.",
